# Worktree Sync and Visibility

- Never leave implementation changes only inside a temporary Cursor worktree path.
- By the end of every user-request reply, all code and documentation changes must exist under the main project workspace sources.
- If a temporary worktree is used for any reason, copy or apply all resulting edits back to the main workspace before reporting completion.
- Never silently keep work in alternate paths; explicitly verify target files are visible in the main workspace tree.
- Before finishing substantial edits, validate visibility by checking key created paths in the main workspace and ensure they appear in `git status`.
